title: For Trade:  Beretta 92SB Compact Type-M
postcontent:
A very scarce Italian made Beretta Model 92SB Compact Type M. Single stack eight round 9mm with 4.25” barrel. Original high polish blue finish is outstanding and looks new, yet this gun has been fired. Factory grips. Includes Beretta case and 2 factory eight round magazines. Only produced in limited quantities for export to the US, only abut 1200 of this model were brought into the country in the late 1980’s. The SB line was the model prior to the 92F and offered high polish blue finish but with many of the standard features you see on 92’s today including ambi safety/decocker and thumb mag release. The single stack “Type M” offers a more compact profile versus the girth of a double stack magazine. This is a very collectible pistol. A nice collector condition Beretta Model 92SB Compact Type M,This is the slim carry model with the single stack 8 round mag.

title: For Sale:  Springfield Armory XD45 Tactical
postcontent:
***IF YOU SEE THIS AD, THE PISTOL IS STILL FOR SALE.  MESSAGES OR EMAILS ASKING IF IT IS STILL AVAILABLE WILL BE IGNORED DUE TO SPAMMERS, SORRY!***

Here's a fun pistol to own: The Springfield Armory XD45 Tactical, striker-fired semi-auto with a 5" barrel, comes with two 13rd magazines, factory box and all paperwork including the fired case with a "born-on" date of 01-06-2011.  I haven't owned it long, but I determined that I've got other firearm itches that need to be scratched, so I'm putting it up now before I get too attached and do something crazy like order a 460 Rowland conversion for it!

I've personally put 50 rounds through it, but I'm not the original owner.  The pistol shows some typical wear on barrel hood that's consistent with an XD that's had a number of rounds through it, but it's in solid mechanical shape.  It does have some bright spots showing at the upper right corner of the slide, but the metal is still protected by the factory melonite finish.

Check out the photo I posted of the first 13 rounds I fired from this pistol!  Yes, the first *13* I fired from this pistol all went into that ~1" hole.  It measures 1.1", center to center, actually.  That was fired from 7 yards, standing offhand using PMC Bronze 230gr ammo.  I know, I know - the group isn't that impressive, but for me it shows this pistol can shoot, even with a hack such as myself behind the trigger!  Speaking of the trigger; it breaks right at 6lbs as measured by my Lyman digital trigger gauge.  It's a smooth break with no stacking or other unpleasantness.  If I didn't tell you I'm sure you'd think it was a lighter trigger.  However, it is a factory trigger so don't think any miracles are happening here. ;)

I'm asking $450.  I'm in absolutely no rush to sell, so please don't bother with lowball offers.  I may be interested in a trade, but no shotguns, please!  Let me know what you have; the worst I can say is no thank you.  Please be ready to send non-blurry, reasonably sized photos of your trade.  I need to be able to see what you're offering. I prefer to do my transactions during daylight hours at the Academy parking lot located at either 1604/Potranco or 410/Military on the SW side of town.  Cash only - no checks or credit cards.

title: For Sale:  S&W M&P 9c - 5 Mags, LH Holster, Night Sights
postcontent:
Up for sale is my S&W M&P 9mm Compact. Great gun, ridiculously reliable. If you've owned or own an M&P, you know how solid these are, and they shoot anything without fail. I have an M&P 9 full size in my nightstand as I type. 

However, I'm looking for a change for my carry piece, maybe something lighter, smaller, I dunno...just something different. 

OK so some history behind this - bought it from a guy a while back, he had done some stippling to the frame, so please be aware of that. It creates excellent grip, but is a different feel from stock. Still extremely comfortable, and even an "upgrade" in a certain way. About 4 months ago, some very minor rust spots formed on the slide...so I contacted S&W who had me mail the gun in. I did, and they refinished the slide...it's beautiful now and not a single speck of rust. Apparently they had some issues with how they'd treated metal on a bunch of guns. It's perfect now.

When they re-did the slide, they did not put the Trijicon night sights back in place. I have not gotten around to installing them, but I have them in a little baggy. Still very bright, with the bright orange circle on the front sight. $60 if interested.

I am going to include 2 mags in my price. These are the 12 round mags, better than the 10 rounders. And, I have the pinky grip piece on them, which I had to buy separately. S&W originals, they work flawlessly.

If you know guns, you know how much of a pain it can be to acquire mags. Sometimes they're damn near unobtainable,or just stupid expensive. So...the 3 extra mags I have will be $40 each if you want them.

Also, I'm a lefty, and I did the whole 2-3 month wait for a Crossbreed Supertuck holster. It was $80 or so, and it's amazing, worth every penny. Obviously, if you're reading this and you're a righty, it does you no good. Just offering it for $60 if interested.

So that's $700 for everything, or just $460 if you want the M&P 9c with 2 12 round mags. Your call, really not willing to wiggle on price.

Open to trades, NO JUNK, and nothing other than guns/ammo. Quality AKs, 1911s, compact Sigs or HKs, quality over/under shotguns, SxS shotguns, quality combo guns (something chambered in shotty shell + rifle), lever action in 357, etc. Open to anything except junk...for handguns, I prefer 9mm, 45ACP, 380Auto, no .40S&W since I've just never gotten into that caliber.

Email me here or call/text 5 one 3 four 6 zero 5 two 7 two.
